Retrieval of graphics memory values.? After the driver model is determined to be WDDM, the application can use the DirectX 10 or later API and DXGI to get the amount of graphics memory.  After creating a Direct3D device the following code can be used to obtain  a  structure containing the amount of available graphics memory.    * pDXGIDevice;	
           hr = g_pd3dDevice->QueryInterface(__uuidof(), (void **)&pDXGIDevice);	
            * pDXGIAdapter;	
           pDXGIDevice->GetAdapter(&pDXGIAdapter);	
            adapterDesc;	
           pDXGIAdapter->GetDesc(&adapterDesc);

